	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Port Elizabeth - President Jacob Zuma has authorised the Special Investigating Unit (SIU) to probe alleged maladministration in the Alfred Nzo district municipality in the Eastern Cape. The Presidency said in a statement on Friday that the proclamation was made in terms of the SIU Act of 1996, and would allow for investigation of allegations including: Presidency spokesperson Bongani Ngqulunga said the SIU brought the issue to Zuma's attention and asked to investigate. The SIU dealt with matters including serious government maladministration, he said. Alfred Nzo is one of six district municipalities in the province. Zuma also authorized a similar investigation into Thabazimbi local municipality in Limpopo, and the Eastern Cape department of social development. *This article has been updated.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  